<br>
&quot;Last night we heard from a player that Brad Mcquaid and Jeff Butler mentioned that traps would be implemented in the Velious expansion. All the details weren't clear but allegedly disarm trap would become a useful skill. Once a rogue detected a trap, disarm trap would enable a rogue to remove it. Traps would be attached to walls or floors and have an agro radius much like a mob does.<br>
<br>
We were pretty excited to hear about this because we know that rogues have been eager to have the disarm skill become useful since the end of BETA. However, we did not hear this from Brad or Jeff's lips ourselves so we looked for confirmation from Gordon Wrinn. Gordon, could not confirm or deny any specific details but did say that disarm trap was going to be addressed eventually. He also said that no new trap specific changes would occur in the initial release of Velious.<br>
<br>
Draw your own conclusions.<br>
<br>
Xomiach<br>
Editor Everlore&quot;<br>
<br>
